enka kanopi — split license
===========================

This repository contains two kinds of work under two different licenses.

Draw the line like this:

  • CODE — everything that makes the site run: `.astro`, `.ts`, `.js`, `.mjs`,
    `.css`, config files, build scripts, and the SVG drawing components in
    `src/components/` considered as source code.
      → MIT License (below, Part A).

  • CONTENT — the writing and the drawings as authored works: the essays in
    `src/content/`, the prose in the page templates, and the diagrams as
    creative/artistic works.
      → Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives 4.0
        International (CC BY-NC-ND 4.0). Summary and pointer below, Part B.

Where a single file mixes both (e.g. a diagram component that is both code and
drawing), the CODE license governs its use as software and the CONTENT license
governs its use as a creative work.

